                                    ======================
                                    USER DEFIEND EXCEPTION
                                    ======================

-> In java language, we have several pre-defined exceptions.

Ex:  IOException, FileNotfound Exception, ClassNotFound Exception, SQL Exception, Arithmetic Exception, ArrayNegativeSize Exception, NullPointerException, ClassCastException etc..

--> Based on project requirement, sometimes we need to create our own exceptions those are called as User Defined Exceptions.

 Ex: InvalidCredentialException, NoRecordFoundExceptions, NoDataFoundExceptions, InvalidInputExceptions,

---> To create our own exception we need to extend the properties from Exception / RuntimeException class.


Example: 


First we need to create one "NoDataFoundException" class in my package , this exception is called USER DEFINED EXCEPTON


NoDataFoundException.java
==========================

package in.psa.userDemo;

public class NoDataFoundException extends RuntimeException{
	
	public NoDataFoundException() {

	
	}
	public NoDataFoundException(String msg) {

		
		super(msg);
	}	

}
===============================================================================
Now we will call this in our programe

Demo5.java
===========

package in.psa.userDemo;
public class Demo5 {

	
	private String getName(int id) {
		
		if(id == 100) {
			
			return "sonu";
		}else if (id == 101) {
			
			return "monu";
		}else {
			
			throw new NoDataFoundException("Invalid Id");
		}
	}
	
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		Demo5 d = new Demo5();
		String name = d.getName(200);
		System.out.println(name);
	}
}


